nts on the council but to see real change in the way in which our borough council prioritises its spending across the town."}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"College","seats":1,"turnout_pct":47.28,"results_url":"https://democracy.cheltenham.gov.uk/mgElectionAreaResults.aspx?XXR=0&ID=139&RPID=176053274","candidates":[{"n":"Garth Wallington Barnes","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1003,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"43797","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/43797/9543a202-dd38-4671-99fd-e5cfc129cd49.png"},{"n":"Naomi Seadon","p":"Green Party","v":337,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"110389"},{"n":"Rich Newman","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":334,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"46700","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/46700/012ecf46-97b8-4eb4-801b-983274f55f6f.png","stmt":". Challenge the Lib Dems\n. Save our town centre \n. Keep our county united as one\n. Stop financial waste at CBC","tw":"\"newman4college\"","bd":"1995"},{"n":"Maureen McNall","p":"Reform UK","v":269,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"127008"},{"n":"Adam Moliver","p":"Labour Party","v":51,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"110356"},{"n":"Stephen Paul Reid","p":"Heritage Party","v":10,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"126984"}],"female_count":2,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Hesters Way","seats":1,"turnout_pct":29.01,"results_url":"https://democracy.cheltenham.gov.uk/mgElectionAreaResults.aspx?XXR=0&ID=140&RPID=176156721","candidates":[{"n":"Callum James Eldridge","p":"Reform UK","v":431,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"127022","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127022/673098dd-fd0b-4c7e-a5a1-5b0a2af224c7.png"},{"n":"Benjamin Botchway","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":415,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"127019","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127019/b9b2f2dc-f6f2-4de5-a31d-b63f538f82c5.png"},{"n":"Wendy Flynn","p":"Green Party","v":366,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"15191","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/15191/41f27841-4a1e-417d-bd62-7c11af2239ce.png","stmt":"I've lived in Hesters Way since 1994 and for 22 years represented Hester’s Way on the Borough Council. After moving to the Green Party 4 years ago because Lib Dems were abandoning their values in order to retain power and votes, I narrowly missed out on being re-elected (by just 68 votes). The Green Party matched my values and ethics and was a natural home.\n\nI've volunteered in various local settings: as a school governor, PTA treasurer, Surestart Board member, Lido Trustee, a Brownie Guider (24 years) and I am currently a Director (Treasurer) of the West Cheltenham Partnership and Vice Chair of the Hesters Way Neighbourhood Planning Forum. I also run a free to attend creative writing group in Hesters Way. I've taken part in litter picks, tree planting, community events, and much more.\n\nIn my Council role, I spoke up for Hester’s Way in committees and meetings both inside and outside the Council. I helped residents with issues such as social housing applications, planning applications, anti-social behaviour, overgrown trees, and refuse collection. As Mayor, in 2013, I challenged how people across the town perceived Hesters Way; I still do this daily.\n\nIn the 2 years I've not been a councillor, I've continued to scrutinise the Lib Dems decisions, on the Household Recycling Centre, their budget, the Golden Valley Development, biodiversity and more. I will continue to use my voice to advocate for west Cheltenham residents, who are my neighbours and my community, regardless of the election result.","tw":"\"wendyflynn\""},{"n":"Alex Miller","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":99,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"127032","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127032/567db9da-7f6e-4b77-a464-db4a0b002690.png"},{"n":"Clive Robert Harriss","p":"Labour Party","v":40,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"15222","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/15222/3fe9343e-8ab8-42e6-9320-a8b52b4724c2.png"},{"n":"Samuel Jacob Coxson","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":8,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"15190","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/77330-72d6edca-021b-435d-957c-d082cee7a77c.png","stmt":"Gloucestershire TUSC Press Release (for immediate release) 24/03/2021\r\n\r\nLocal councils are facing a new Covid-driven cash crisis. Our communities have already suffered more than a decade of austerity and now face more cuts to public services. Councils are massively underfunded by central Government and Covid-19 has revealed the difficulties local councils face in meeting the needs of people.\r\n\r\nThe Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition (TUSC) was formed in 2010 to provide an anti-austerity political voice for working class people. Councils of all political persuasion have continued to implement austerity cuts to local services. TUSC is different from other parties. TUSC councillors will oppose all cuts to council jobs and services. \r\n\r\nTUSC is standing hundreds of candidates nationally in the May election. TUSC candidates include trade unionists, socialists, and social movement and community campaigners standing against pro-austerity establishment politicians.\r\n\r\nGloucestershire has fifteen TUSC candidates standing in twenty seats in Cheltenham, Stroud, Cirencester, the Forest of Dean and Gloucester.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTUSC candidates will refuse to implement austerity and will oppose all cuts to council services, jobs, pay and conditions. They will oppose policies designed to make ordinary people pay for the Covid-crisis.  In the short-term Councils could use reserves and borrowing to avoid making cuts in local services and in the longer-term can build linked mass campaigns to demand that central Government restores the funding it has cut. \r\n\r\n\r\nTUSC candidates will not vote for council tax increases or increases in council rent to bridge the gap in funding from central Government.\r\n\r\nTUSC candidates will propose the use of the powers that local councils already have to begin a mass building programme of eco-friendly affordable council homes.\r\n \r\nTUSC councillors will vote against privatisation of council jobs and services where central Government is attempting to impose","tw":"\"TUSCGlos\"","bd":"1991"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":5,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Lansdown","seats":1,"turnout_pct":46.29,"results_url":"https://democracy.cheltenham.gov.uk/mgElectionAreaResults.aspx?ID=141&RPID=176130236","candidates":[{"n":"Jamie Jamieson","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":874,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"127043","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127043/25e78700-ed37-46a9-accd-84c17fc0570b.png"},{"n":"Pippa Mason","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":574,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127044","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127044/2992f594-e978-4d6d-be01-b15e1b52d542.png"},{"n":"Ed Joy","p":"Green Party","v":330,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"125531","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/125531/f1bd6a2f-2f44-4903-bfad-a0c24f94143d.png"},{"n":"Dean Raymond Luke Botterill","p":"Reform UK","v":324,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"120073","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127040/d1fc056d-4d45-4a26-a705-d03eb43c75b6.png"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Leckhampton","seats":1,"turnout_pct":58.32,"results_url":"https://democracy.cheltenham.gov.uk/mgElectionAreaResults.aspx?XXR=0&ID=142&RPID=176070129","candidates":[{"n":"Julia Caroline Chandler","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1274,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"110362","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/110362/8c78a6be-06c8-4e1c-ac5e-218c2561350f.png","stmt":"Julia Chandler has lived in Leckhampton for 26 years and is the Liberal Democrat candidate for the borough council in May’s election, alongside Martin. Julia was an NHS nurse and midwife. She has worked at both Cheltenham General and Gloucestershire Royal Hospitals and as a community midwife. More recently she worked for the Royal College of Midwives as a professional advisor and ‘critical friend’ to NHS England.  Back in 2006 she worked closely with Martin to launch the Cheltenham Maternity Matters campaign that saved Cheltenham's maternity unit.  Councils have an important role scrutinising local health services. If elected, Julia wants to be a ‘critical friend’ to the local NHS too, arguing for the right decisions for local people. She's already backing Max Wilkinson’s petition for an additional GP surgery for Cheltenham."},{"n":"Nick Saywell","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":491,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"110342","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/110342/3357fa2b-844b-4a4b-97f7-9927b4619f32.png"},{"n":"Stephen Hayward Bajdala-Brown","p":"Reform UK","v":307,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"127058"},{"n":"Peter Frings","p":"Green Party","v":260,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"42054","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/42054-368092d2-0e52-4c3f-bd6b-a4630a01c6f1.png","stmt":"Peter joined Leckhampton Parish Council in 2018, and acts as Chair of the Air Pollution committee.\r\n\r\nHe has over 35 years' experience in the marketing services industry and has an Executive MBA. Peter moved to Cheltenham in the 1990s and founded a business here in 2002 that's been one of the fastest growing businesses in Gloucestershire for 15 years, creating more than 120 local jobs in Cheltenham in that time.\r\n\r\nPeter has lived in the Leckhampton ward for the last 8 years, and stepped back from full-time work in 2017, although continues to work part-time as a business and marketing consultant.\r\n\r\nPeter has a degree in Biology and Ecology and has been interested in green issues since the 1970s. His main priorities on the Parish Council are working on air pollution and sustainable transport, and enhancing Leckhampton's green spaces. He's also one of the founding members of Clean Air Cheltenham.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time, he enjoys cycling, walking and growing organic vegetables.","tw":"\"PeterFrings\""},{"n":"Philip Cole","p":"Labour Party","v":33,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"127059"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Oakley","seats":1,"turnout_pct":36.18,"results_url":"https://democracy.cheltenham.gov.uk/mgElectionAreaResults.aspx?ID=143&RPID=176147037","candidates":[{"n":"Alisha Chloe-Marie Lewis","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":632,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"35925","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/35925/552de13f-8155-4111-aa62-d65108275092.png","tw":"\"Alishacmlewis\""},{"n":"Maureen Susan Dodwell","p":"Reform UK","v":487,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existin